This goes out to everyone thats been doing keep taking against defended keeps.<P>Are you having serious problems taking defended keeps against hibs and mids that have a couple people spamming ground target AoE against people on the doors, or they go up into the lord room and spam it into that narrow hallway.  Albs on my server are having serious issues against this, we had a huge force against maybe 15-20 hibs tops and we couldnt get Eras back.  <BR>When we finally got through the door (basically had two people build and control rams while healers spammed a low level heal on them, and everyone else sat back and tried to kill the occasional wall troll)  Nobody can even get into the camped lord room with any kinda health at all due to them spamming that GTAoE into the hallway.  Plus with 0 earth wizzys we cant fire back like they do, my only offense I could muster was to get a pet that could DD like a iso wizard or a iso scout with its bow and no LOS and shoot whoever I could target in that lord room through the walls, but that was more of a nuisance then anything else.<BR>Mids did pretty much the same thing against us, I think we got maybe one keep back that was defended like that simply becuase they only had one person doing it, instead of multiple like the rest of the encounters.<P>Does this spell have no LoS restrictions like it should?  I also notice that its AoE area is like a bubble, and not a flat circle which really killed us when you start approaching them on the stairs.  And the damage didnt seem to trail off the farther you got away from the center of the radius either.<P>Guess I'm just kinda annoyed with the lack of testing on this spell, cause its severly overpowered right now as it is in my opinion.<P>--------------------<P>Isudus<BR>L50 Sorcerer of Tristan
