Has anyone developed a working tactic against this yet?<P>I have a trick that may work with good teamplay, but never tried this out.<BR>	<BR>First send one Tank with a lot of HPs fully buffed and resisted up to the keeplord.<BR>His mission is to reach the window in the lord room, so that I can select him. It doesn't matter if he dies. The reasen is to give me a target where I can send a fast L50 pet (passiv mode).<BR>As soon as I can see the pet, I relase it and try to cast qc mezz, so that the complete lordroom should be mezzed. Maybe a minstel should instant stun the pet after release to make sure that it stays where it is. The only problem is that the pet need to stay long enough alive to cast mezz. A cleric could also help if he heals the pet with instant heal befor the release.<P>I don't see any reasen why we shouldn't be able to send our pet somewhere without a spezial target.<BR>Like I get a target with siege weapons. This would us give more possible tactics like this I think....<P>--------------------<P>Econ<BR>L50 MindSorcerer on Lyonesse<BR>_ _____________________________ _ <P><B>€XP€XT TH€ UN€XP€CT€D</B> <P><I><B>Beowolve</B></I>
